---
import { siteConfig } from "../data/docs";
---

<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="shell site-footer__inner">
    <div>
      <p class="site-footer__title">{siteConfig.name}</p>
      <p>
        A Sprite-first remote coding runtime that gives agents real Linux tools,
        focused MCP commands, and read-first GitHub access.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="site-footer__title">Access model</p>
      <p>
        Reader app access stays on for clone and fetch workflows. Push access is
        temporary, repo-scoped, device-flow approved, and revoked after use.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="site-footer__title">Repository</p>
      <p>
        Inspect the Rust runtime, operator CLI, Sprite setup path, GitHub grant
        helpers, and MCP server implementation in the project repository.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</footer>
